<TITLE> Bhola fisherman dies in gunfight between coastguards, pirates </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bhola, July 9 (bdnews24.com) -- At least one fisherman died and four others were injured in a gun-battle between Bangladesh Coastguard and alleged pirates on the Meghna River in Bhola Sunday. OC Syed Robiul Islam of Tozumuddin Police Station said, "The fishermen were unfortunately caught up in a gun-battle between the Coastguard and suspected pirates, which left one dead and four wounded." Coastguard commander ATM Ashraf added: "A contingent of the coastguard, on a regular patrol, encountered a suspected pirates' trawler and gave chase at around 10 pm." The pirates opened fire prompting 16 shots from the coastguard. Ashraf could not confirm any casualties. The deceased has been identified as Kamal Hossain, 30, from South Aicha village, Char Fashion. The four injured were Nirab, 25, Ayub Ali, 22, Kamal, 22 and Jamal, 23. bdnews24.com/
